Sentencas: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs) use the same materials as electrode, thereby reducing fabrication processes, simplifying interface problem and improving tolerance to coking and sulfur.
Titulo: Multifunctional perovskite oxide Sr 2 Ti 1- x Ni x FeO 6-δ ( x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: In this paper, the multifunctional Sr2Ti0.8Ni0.2FeO6-delta (STN02F) oxide is successfully synthesized and evaluated to be as symmetrical electrodes for SOFCs.
Titulo: Multifunctional perovskite oxide Sr 2 Ti 1- x Ni x FeO 6-δ ( x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The Ni-Fe alloy nanoparticles can be exsolved from STN02F sample in high temperature reducing atmosphere.
Titulo: Multifunctional perovskite oxide Sr 2 Ti 1- x Ni x FeO 6-δ ( x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The impedance stability test demonstrates that the polarization resistance (Rp) of STN02F exhibited no obvious change in both air and H2.
Titulo: Multifunctional perovskite oxide Sr 2 Ti 1- x Ni x FeO 6-δ ( x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The fuel cells obtain the maximum power densities of 710 mW cm-2 in H2, 581 mW cm-2 in CH3OH, 527 mW cm-2 in C3H8 and 213 mW cm-2 in direct C at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Multifunctional perovskite oxide Sr 2 Ti 1- x Ni x FeO 6-δ ( x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The fuel cell exhibited no output performance degradation during the 200 h test in H2.
Titulo: Multifunctional perovskite oxide Sr 2 Ti 1- x Ni x FeO 6-δ ( x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The current densities of 0.84 A cm-2 at 1.3 V in 50%H2O/50%H2 and 0.77 A cm-2 at 1.5 V in CO2 were obtained for electrolysis cell at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Multifunctional perovskite oxide Sr 2 Ti 1- x Ni x FeO 6-δ ( x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The efficient and stable symmetrical electrode STN02F is a promising candidate material for SOCs.
Titulo: Multifunctional perovskite oxide Sr 2 Ti 1- x Ni x FeO 6-δ ( x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells
